$ SQL Server function: is_member
@ is_member

`is_member` can be used if a given login (default: current execution context) is member of a → Windows/user-account/group[Windows group] or a *SQL Server database role*.

sa:
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions/security/is_srvrolemember[`is_srvrolemember()`]
